The Kerala government today sought a central assistance of Rs 1843 crore in the wake of cyclone Ockhi devastating the state’s coastal stretches, leaving 37 dead and several others missing. Kerala Chief Minister Pinarayi Vijayan on Saturday met Home minister Rajnath Singh and Defence minister Nirmala Sitharaman, in Delhi and apprised them of the situation in the state post Ockhi.
